title: WWE Jakked
overview: WWE Jakked (originally known as WWF Jakked) was a professional wrestling television program produced by the World Wrestling Federation (now known as WWE). This series aired syndicated weekly on Saturdays at midnight from 1999 until 2002 and replaced WWF Shotgun Saturday Night. Originally produced under the World Wrestling Federation (WWF) banner, they were replaced by the similarly formatted WWE Bottom Line and WWE Afterburn in syndication.
